law.text:
Bonds are securities:
in which any of the following persons may legally and properly invest money, including capital that the person owns or controls:
an officer or unit of the State or a political subdivision;
a bank, trust company, savings and loan association, investment company, or other person conducting a banking business;
an insurance company, insurance association, or other person conducting an insurance business;
a personal representative, guardian, trustee, or other fiduciary; and
any other person; and
that may be deposited with and received by a unit of the State or a political subdivision for any purpose for which the deposit of bonds or other obligations of the State is authorized by law.
